<br>
Like they are designed they were never meant to heal our pet completly. Just a portion of its health, to keep it alive a bit longer for those situations where a fight is close. Using a pet heal then shifts the balance and helps you to try being able to win.<br>
<br>
Nukes were always more efficient. And they are by far more defining for the mage class. Pet heals are just a means of support to shift the balance a bit in a hard fight. With the mana effficiency they have they were not intended to heal your pet after a fight when it is nearly dead. You are better off to summon a new pet. Thats also a reason why we get relcaim pet spell (and that effect on many items) and later improved reclaim as an alt exp skill.<br>
<br>
We (mages) are different from beastlords, who are way better in helping their pets, in my opinion also a reason why they get a &quot;pet&quot; (its an animal, not summoned matter) that zones with them and stays with them when they log out and in. I see beastlords as a good class to be compared with mages. They are totally diffenrent but then so similar. We deal quick damage and better damage with our elementals. They deal slower damage, but have better utility for their animal companion. So, also from an RP viewpoint I dont see any probs with our heals being not as efficient as our nukes.<br>
<br>
They were never intended to be as efficient as our nukes. Look at the mage class and tell me we have much utility around pet that does NOT increase its fight power. We are based on fast damage, not suporting our pet in a long fight. We try to prevent long fights and have a bit more downtime as a result.<br>
<br>
IF PoP pets have significantly more HP than the old lvl 60- pets then I would see a heal spell at 65 reasonable. It should not heal more than 25-35% of a pet. IF the new PoP pets are more in the direction of better DMG migitation or faster/higher damage I dont see the need for a new heal.<br>
<br>
If mages ask for a CH type spell for pets thats like a cleric asking for a wizzie like nuke (lowered mana efficiency of course, but still around the same damage).<br>
<br>
VI never intended chaining pets maybe. But players again being smarter than the designers developed this strategy and it showed to be very mana efficient. Now asking those same designers to give us a pet heal that can compete with chain casting pets is kind of ridiculous. If we would get a CH type of spell that would mean we would have to get a significant recast delay (like a few mins) on normal pets also, like the epic. Then it would be reasonable to ask for a CH type spell.<br>
<br>
Think about it.<br>
<br>
I feel like the pet heals are right in line and dont need an upgrade. Though the recast time on mend companion is ridiculous, should be indeed around 72 mins and not 144.<br>
<br>
Greets ... Mel<br>
