I did some experimenmting, and indeed it seems to me that nuking the mobs is more effective than healing in a one on one fight.  So hats off to this thread!! its improved my soloing a little =).  I also decided to examine when I use the heal the most, and determined its not when the pet is ultra low in a close fight (although I cast it then I do not find myself in that situation frequently).  The time I use it the most is when Im dealing with adds like 2 or 3 mobs at once.  THen healing the pet not only buys me time, and keeps me alive, but his ds damages all the mobs generating no agro for me, while nukes would do the opposite.  Again healing and nuking the one he is on is the best combination, and would be impossible with no heals.  I wonder if that situatino is common enough among all mages to warrent more examination with some numbers.  I find myself on two all the time (solo in caves and sorta tight places a lot where moving a tad one way or the other gets adds, of if two pop to fast or something).  Three is kinda rare, but two happens probably a few times an hour.  Just some thoughts.<br>
